#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:1
msgid "eHealth and eFact Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:4
msgid ""
"Configure your nursing home's (MR/MRS) eHealth and eFact settings: "
"certificate, platform, Walloon Account C, CIN license and invoicing "
"header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:8
msgid "Should I choose the Acceptance or Production environment?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:9
msgid ""
"Stay on Acceptance (test servers, no real data) as long as your "
"submissions have not been validated by the CIN and AViQ. Switch to "
"Production only once accreditation is obtained: from then on, submissions"
" actually bill the health insurance funds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:11
msgid "Where do I get the eHealth certificate and the CIN Package License?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:12
msgid ""
"The .p12 certificate is obtained from the eHealth portal "
"(ehealth.fgov.be), after registering the institution and appointing the "
"access manager. The Package License (username and password) is issued by "
"the CIN/NIC when the software is accredited. These elements never appear "
"in plain text in the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:14
msgid "Should stub mode be disabled?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:15
msgid ""
"Stub mode simulates eHealth responses so you can test without a real "
"call. Leave it enabled during the test phase; disable it in production, "
"which requires a valid eHealth certificate and a configured CIN Package "
"License."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:17
msgid "Why fill in a coordinating physician?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:18
msgid ""
"Their NIHII number acts as the responsible practitioner on eAgreement "
"requests when the Katz assessor has no personal NIHII. It is mandatory "
"for a category D Katz, which requires a physician."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:20
msgid "Is Account C mandatory for eFact in Wallonia?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:21
msgid ""
"Yes. In a Walloon MR/MRS, the insurer pays the flat-rate fees to "
"financial account C. Without a C bank journal filled in, WalCareNet "
"rejects the batch (104511 for the missing IBAN, 105311 for the missing "
"BIC)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:23
msgid "Which value should I choose for the Invoice Type (Z308)?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:24
msgid ""
"Leave 01 (Hospitalisation) by default: it is the value accepted at the "
"931000 preliminary check. Only switch to 03 (Ambulatory) if the CIN or "
"AViQ confirms it for your sector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:27
msgid ""
"This screen brings together the **technical credentials and choices** "
"that Resthome uses to communicate with the Belgian e-health ecosystem "
"(eHealth, MyCareNet, WalCareNet): [MDA](../ehealth/mda.md) insurability, "
"[eFact](../ehealth/efact.md) billing and "
"[eAgreement](../ehealth/eagreement.md) agreements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:33
msgid "The settings are split across **two tabs**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:35
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home**: the **eHealth** part (certificate, platform,"
" automation, responsible practitioner, CIN license)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:37
msgid ""
"**Settings > MR/MRS**: the **Walloon billing** part (Account C and eFact "
"header)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:40
msgid ""
"Most of these values are set **once**, at start-up, and then only change "
"marginally afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "Sensitive fields — no value is ever copied from documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:46
msgid ""
"The **.p12 certificate**, the **CIN Package License** and the "
"**passwords** are secrets **specific to your establishment**. Here we "
"explain **what they are for** and **where to obtain them** (eHealth "
"portal, CIN/NIC), never their content. Do not share them, and enter them "
"only from the official source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:52
msgid "eHealth Platform"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:54
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home > eHealth Platform.** The foundation: which "
"identity, which environment and which platform Resthome uses for all "
"exchanges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "Setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "What it is for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "Recommended value (MR/MRS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Active Certificate**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"The eHealth **.p12** certificate that authenticates the institution and "
"signs the SOAP messages. Import it first under *eHealth / Certificates*, "
"then select it here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"**Your establishment's** certificate, obtained from **ehealth.fgov.be**. "
"Never a copied value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Institution INAMI Number**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"Your institution's INAMI/RIZIV number, used in the STS, MDA, eFact and "
"eAgreement requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Your number**: 8 digits (institution) or 11 digits (NIHII-11)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Competence Code**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"The last 3 digits of the NIHII-11 (MR/MRS only, not CSJ); fallback when "
"the certified NIHII-11 cannot be read from the token."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**110** (MR) or **210** (some MRS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Legal Interest Rate (%)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"The annual Belgian legal rate used to calculate the late-payment interest"
" an insurer owes on a submission paid past the deadline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "The **rate published for the year**; **0** disables the calculation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Care Provider NIHII**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"The **personal** NIHII-11 of the caregiver (nurse, physician) who issues "
"the MDA insurability requests — required by WalCareNet/MyCareNet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "The NIHII of the **care provider at your establishment** (11 digits)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Environment**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"*Acceptance* = test servers (simulated data); *Production* = real servers"
" (real billing)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"**Acceptance** as long as not validated, then **Production** after "
"accreditation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Default Platform**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"The target network: WalCareNet (AViQ, Wallonia), MyCareNet (federal), "
"IrisCareNet (Brussels, MDA)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**WalCareNet** for a Walloon MR/MRS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "**Stub Mode (Development)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid "Simulates eHealth responses without a real call — for testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:43
msgid ""
"**Enabled** in test; **disabled** in production (requires a valid "
"certificate + CIN license)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "Start cautiously"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:71
msgid ""
"At start-up: **Acceptance + Stub Mode enabled**. You validate the whole "
"flow without sending anything real. Once accreditation is obtained, "
"switch **Stub Mode disabled**, then **Production**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:76
msgid "eHealth Automation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:78
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home > eHealth Automation.** The automatic "
"behaviours around insurability and logs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Auto MDA Check**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"Automatically checks each resident's insurability before generating the "
"eFact — avoids rejections for invalid insurability (see "
"[MDA](../ehealth/mda.md))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Enabled** as soon as the MDA is in production."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Log Retention (days)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"Number of days communication and audit logs are kept; the oldest are "
"purged by the monthly cron."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**2555** (7 years, Belgian legal requirement for health data)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**No-Facet Report Email**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"Address used by the *Report to intermut* button on an MDA request that "
"remained \"no-facet\" (no insurer answered within 24 h) — to be escalated"
" to the CIN/intermut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "Leave the default **intermut** address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:87
msgid "Software Service Desk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:89
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home > Software Service Desk.** The **first point of"
" contact** when a provider has a problem — an AViQ accreditation "
"requirement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Service Desk Contact**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"The software publisher's contact (name, email, phone, logo), shown by the"
" *Contact LPLG* button on eAgreement requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "Leave the default **LPLG contact**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:96
msgid "eAgreement Responsible Practitioner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:98
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home > eAgreement Responsible Practitioner.** On an "
"[eAgreement](../ehealth/eagreement.md) request, the responsible "
"practitioner is the clinician who carried out the Katz assessment. If "
"they have no personal NIHII, the request borrows the identity of the head"
" nurse, then of the coordinating physician."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Head Nurse (NIHII fallback)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"Their NIHII identifies the responsible practitioner when the Katz "
"assessor (nurse, care assistant) has no NIHII."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "Fill in the establishment's **head nurse**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "**Coordinating Physician (NIHII fallback)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid ""
"Fallback when no nurse NIHII is available, and **mandatory** for a "
"category D Katz (physician required)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:68
msgid "Fill in the **coordinating physician** — essential for category D Katz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "The Katz category is for declaring, not for setting the amount"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:112
msgid ""
"The **dependency flat rate** is the **same amount** for all Katz "
"categories (AViQ tariffs); the category serves to **declare the "
"resident's profile** to the health insurance fund. A category **D** "
"nonetheless requires a **physician** as the eAgreement's responsible "
"practitioner — hence the importance of this field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:118
msgid "CIN Package License"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:120
msgid ""
"**Settings > Nursing Home > CIN Package License.** The credentials that "
"authorise Resthome to send via GenAsync (eFact) and CommonInput (MDA)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "**Package License Username**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "Username of the software license, required for eFact and MDA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "Provided by the **CIN/NIC** at accreditation — specific to your software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "**Package License Password**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "Password of the software license (masked field)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:109
msgid "Provided by the **CIN/NIC**; **secret**, do not disclose it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
msgid "Where to obtain it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:131
msgid ""
"The Package License is issued by the **CIN/NIC** when the software is "
"accredited. It has **no default value**: as long as it is not configured "
"(and stub mode disabled), real submissions remain blocked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:136
msgid "Account C (Wallonia)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:138
msgid ""
"**Settings > MR/MRS > Account C (Wallonia).** Since the 6th State Reform,"
" the insurer pays the Walloon MR/MRS flat-rate fees to a dedicated "
"**financial account C**, declared to the CIN during eFact registration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
msgid "**Account C Bank Journal**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
msgid ""
"The bank journal of the Walloon account. The **IBAN** (ET 10 Z 45-47a) "
"and the **BIC** (Z 53-54a) written in the 920000 are derived from it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:128
msgid ""
"Your establishment's **Account C journal**. Fill in the IBAN on the bank "
"account and the BIC on the bank."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "Otherwise, WalCareNet rejection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:149
msgid ""
"Without a valid Account C, WalCareNet **rejects the batch**: **104511** "
"(missing IBAN) or **105311** (missing BIC). The IBAN and BIC shown under "
"the field are read-only — they come from the journal's bank account. See "
"[eFact Rejections](../ehealth/efact-rejets.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:155
msgid "eFact Header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:157
msgid ""
"**Settings > MR/MRS > eFact Header.** The header information carried by "
"each [eFact](../ehealth/efact.md) 920000 message (segment 300)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "**eFact Contact Person**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid ""
"Name and phone written in the header (Z305 surname / Z306 first name / "
"Z307 phone) — the person an insurer contacts for a billing question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid ""
"For example, the establishment's **director**. If empty, the "
"establishment name is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid "**eFact Invoice Type (Z308)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid ""
"The Z308 \"invoice type\" zone: 01 Hospitalisation, 03 Ambulatory, 09 "
"Mixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-ehealth.md:146
msgid ""
"**01** by default (accepted at the 931000 check). Only switch to **03** "
"if AViQ/CIN confirms it."
msgstr ""

